               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Fīhi mā fih by Rūmī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85084471" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_694-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian and Arabic </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1197">Fīhi mā fih</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1197">فيه ما فيه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Substantial fragment from the mystical treatise collecting biographical anecdotes and maxims from the life of the Sufi poet and saint <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100166176928.0x000001 viaf_98930150" role="aut">Jalāl al-Dīn al-Balkhī Rūmī</persName> (d. 672/1273), compiled by his son <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_66900471" role="aut">Sulṭān Valad or Bahāʾ al-Dīn Muḥammad</persName> (d. 712/1312). 
                        </p>
                        <p>The work is divided into seventy-two discourses. 
</p>
                        <p>Defective at end. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. Datable to the late seventeenth century. 
</p>
                        <p>Shikastah āmīz. 
</p>
                        <p>Not foliated. 
</p>
                        <p>Lacking original binding. 
</p>
                        <p>Binding damaged (combed marble paper with brown leather edging over delaminating pasteboards), labels. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_98930150">Rūmī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_98930150">رومى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
